<h3><FONT COLOR=green>Current Projects</FONT></h3>
	  <ul>
<li> Synthesis for system design: <a href="http://excape.cis.upenn.edu/">NSF Expeditions project in Computer Augmented Program Engineering</a>
		  <li>Architecture aware analysis of concurrent software
(<a href="http://checkfence.sourceforge.net/">Checkfence</a>)
<li><a href=nw.html>Nested Words (aka visibly pushdown languages)</a> for modeling linear-hierarchical structure (with applications
to model checking of structured programs and document processing) 
<li>Design, implementation, and scheduling of embedded software
(<a href="http://www.seas.upenn.edu/~gera/RTComposer.html">RTComposer </a>)
<li>Symbolic simulation for hybrid systems analysis
	<li>Recent projects:
Automated symbolic compositional verification by learning assumptions,
JIST (Interfaces for Java classes using abstraction and games),
<a href=scenarios.html>Specification, Analysis, and Testing of Scenario-based Requirements.</a>, HERMES (Model Checking of Hierarchical State Machines),
<a href="http://www.cis.upenn.edu/~mocha/">Mocha</a> (Model checking of open systems using ATL), <a href="http://www.cis.upenn.edu/mobies/charon/"> CHARON </a> (Hybrid systems: modeling and verification),
Timed and hybrid automata
		 </ul>


